{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d7cbef2c-4894-4fa8-94d8-8a8272e50428","content":"The issue is clear — F# requires files to be listed in dependency order in the `.fsproj`. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Domain.fs` is listed after `Services.fs`.\n\nFixing the compile order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_LLl638PwuZrnluwTaxfxUD","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-e705cbe743704f8198d8f6963b09296e/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-e705cbe743704f8198d8f6963b09296e/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"9e6bb2d8-f24f-4115-b80f-579f5b62effd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters because files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear *before* them in the project file. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n```xml\n<Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n```\n\n`Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` is listed *after* `Services.fs`. Similarly, `Program.fs` opens both `BrokenOrder.Domain` and `BrokenOrder.Services`, which is fine since both appear before it... wait, no. \n\n`Domain.fs` appears after `Services.fs`, so `Services.fs` can't reference `Domain.fs`. The fix is straightforward: reorder the files so `Domain.fs` comes first since it has no dependencies, then `Services.fs` which depends on it, and finally `Program.fs` which depends on both.","outputTokens":518,"requestId":"5BD8:1F0E10:48CB432:5056CE0:69F9E5E2"},"id":"fad927d7-5fe9-479d-bbd0-f6d2847bc555","timestamp":"2026-05-05T12:43:22.806Z","parentId":"8c416431-6cd7-4130-bb97-886f5a9a04a9"}
